# Claude skills (user-local)

This repo’s **Seldon skill** (`.agents/skills/seldon/SKILL.md`) is
canonical for **this codebase**. For **cross-cutting topics**, also load the
matching skill from your **Claude skills** directory when relevant:

| Topic                                            | Skill folder (each contains `SKILL.md`)                   |
| ------------------------------------------------ | --------------------------------------------------------- |
| Sanity schemas, GROQ, Portable Text, preview     | `~/.claude/skills/sanity-best-practices`                  |
| SEO, metadata, structured data, hreflang         | `~/.claude/skills/seo-aeo-best-practices`                 |
| CMS/content architecture, references vs embedded | `~/.claude/skills/content-modeling-best-practices`        |
| Experiments, A/B tests, metrics                  | `~/.claude/skills/content-experimentation-best-practices` |
| Discovering or installing skills                 | `~/.claude/skills/find-skills`                            |

**Paths:** Skills live under **`~/.claude/skills/<name>/SKILL.md`**. Install or
update with **`npx skills add`** / **`npx skills update`** (Skills CLI) — see
**`docs/agents/SETUP.md`**. Project-bundled skills also live under
**`.agents/skills/`** (committed or symlinked); user-local copies may live under
`~/.claude/skills`.

**When to use:** Prefer project docs (`AGENTS.md`, `docs/agents/*`, Seldon skill)
first; pull in a Claude skill when you need deeper domain guidance that
complements (not replaces) repo conventions.
